ABUJA – The Federal Capital Territo­ry Administration (FCTA) Permanent Secretary, Mr. Olusade Adesola, has said that milk production in Abu­ja, has climbed from 150 litres to 1500 litres per day over the last two years. He stated this at the FCT Grazing Reserve, Paikon-Ko­re, Gwagwalada, Abuja, on the occasion of the com­memoration of 2022 World Milk Day 2022, in conjunc­tion with CBI Nestle Foods Plc, and other stakeholders in the livestock development value chain. The Permanent Secretary, who was represented by Mr. Samuel Atang, Director Op­erations, Planning, and Strat­egy in the Permanent Secre­tary’s Office, stated that the administration, through its relevant SDAs such as the Ag­riculture and Rural Develop­ment Secretariat (ARDS), has made significant progress. -Advertisement- According to him, the theme of this year’s event, “Sustainability in The Dairy Sector as Well as En­vironmental, National and Socio-economic Empower­ment” is aimed at lowering greenhouse emission and im­proving waste management in the next 30 years.